net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component

Class Checkbox

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
      • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.AbstractButton
        • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ToggleButton
          • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.Checkbox
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Iterable<Component>, LocaleContextSource, CardContainerSelector, Component, ListCellRenderer, TableCellEditor, TableCellRenderer, TreeCellEditor, TreeCellRenderer
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BooleanValueEditor

    @UIElement(supportsAction=true,
           name="checkbox")
@Configurable
public class Checkbox
extends ToggleButton
implements TableCellEditor, TreeCellEditor
    A component that represents a check box that can be toggled on and off. The click() may or may not be called. Listen to ItemEvent events to detect when the state is changed.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • getHTMLElement

        public Element getHTMLElement()
        Description copied from interface: Component
        Get the top level elements this component will output in its current state. This should not included the entire content model.

        For example, if your code outputs the following, <p><span><b></b></span></p>, then you should only return one element that is a "p"; NOT "p, span, b".

        All configuration elements should be nested within this top element, or other arrangements should be made with the inner keeper.

        Specified by:
        getHTMLElement in interface Component
        Overrides:
        getHTMLElement in class AbstractButton
        Returns:
        the element.

      • getTableCellEditorComponent

        public Component getTableCellEditorComponent(Table table,
                                    Object value,
                                    boolean isSelected,
                                    int row,
                                    int column)
        Calls the getTableCellRendererComponent() method and enables the component.

        Returns a Component to use for editing a cell in a table.

        Note to implementers of this interface: If you write a class that implements this interface and returns another TableCellEditor capable Component, be sure to call the other Component's getTableCellEditorComponent() method.

        Specified by:
        getTableCellEditorComponent in interface TableCellEditor
        Parameters:
        table - The Table that has the data being edited.
        value - The value of the cell being edited.
        isSelected - Indicates whether the cell is in a selected state.
        row - The row for the cell.
        column - The column model index (NOT the model index!).
        Returns:
        An object that is a Component which can be used to edit the value stored in the specified table cell.

      • preRenderProcess

        public void preRenderProcess(Request request,
                    Response response,
                    RendererEditorState<?> rendererEditorState)
        Description copied from class: AbstractButton
        Allow the component to process any form fields before rendering. This method must be called by subclasses. Method calls on components, creating or destroying components, or nearly everything else having to do with the component tree and related data models must be done by queuing an event using EventQueue.queue(EventQueueElement). Otherwise you may get unexpected results. Calls AbstractButton.click() on the button and sets the selection path if the renderer state is not null.
        Specified by:
        preRenderProcess in interface Component
        Overrides:
        preRenderProcess in class AbstractButton
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        response - the response.
        rendererEditorState - the renderer / editor state, will be null if not using as a renderer / editor.

      • setHTMLElement

        public void setHTMLElement(HTMLElement element)
        Set the HTMLElement.

        Special support is available for HTMLElement.label. For label, the inner label is not output - the container is the label. Other common elements are HTMLElement.li, HTMLElement.div, HTMLElement.p, and HTMLElement.span.

        By default it is a HTMLElement.span.

        Parameters:
        element - the element.
